<subSubSection id="ACA76575FFBC424FD4C51762FAEDFD98" box="[245,1295,602,625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E40236FEFFBC424FD4C51762FAEDFD98" blockId="6.[151,1435,221,625]" box="[245,1295,602,625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="D6C9EAECFFBC424FD4C51762FE97FD98" bold="true" box="[245,373,602,625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="23BD4D7DFFBC424FD66F1762FD7EFD98" box="[607,668,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">rufus</taxonomicName>
”, meaning red, refers to the red lateral markings on crown.
</paragraph>
